snippet.textDisplay:
For those who don't know the tale...

It describes how Sir Gaiwan, a knight of King Arthur''s Round Tabe, accepts a challenge from a mysterious "Green Knight" who dares any knight to strike him with his axe if he will take a return blow in a year and a day. Gawain accepts and beheads him with his blow, at which the Green Knight stands up, picks up his head and reminds Gawain of the appointed time. In his struggles to keep his bargain, Gawain demonstrates chivalry and loyalty until his honour is called into question by a test involving Lady Bertilak, the lady of the Green Knight's castle.

snippet.textDisplay:
3 ‘MAD MEN’


I have been running into ‘madmen’ on the street recently. It happened three times so I guess I should write about it. One was well dressed but three steps away from me he spat on the ground and started cursing me for no reason. I kept a wary eye on him as he passed ready for any attack. The second one was standing as I passed, and he playfully took his shirt and struck me across my torso. He smiled, so I smiled back resisting the temptation to be annoyed and upset. The third one approach us and began to search a garbage bin for food right there in front of everybody unashamed and purposeful. The first two were insane, a third could have been just homeless. JESUS has a salvation plan for everybody, even the ‘insane’. Love them, He died for them too.
snippet.textOriginal:
3 ‘MAD MEN’


I have been running into ‘madmen’ on the street recently. It happened three times so I guess I should write about it. One was well dressed but three steps away from me he spat on the ground and started cursing me for no reason. I kept a wary eye on him as he passed ready for any attack. The second one was standing as I passed, and he playfully took his shirt and struck me across my torso. He smiled, so I smiled back resisting the temptation to be annoyed and upset. The third one approach us and began to search a garbage bin for food right there in front of everybody unashamed and purposeful. The first two were insane, a third could have been just homeless. JESUS has a salvation plan for everybody, even the ‘insane’. Love them, He died for them too.
